cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel approach for learning a joint distribution of multi-domain images using generative adversarial networks. The approach is applied to several tasks including color and depth images, and face images with different attributes. These tasks are closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses domain adaptation and image transformation, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multimedia (cs.MM), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
